## Scaling
<p align ="left"><font color="yellow">Specification</font></p>
<img wigth ="400" height="400" src="lectures/2/fig/image18.JPG" align ="left">
<p align ="left"><font size="5">Vectorially we get:</font></p>
<p align ="right"><p align ="botton"><font color="#2EFE2E" size ="5">
$\begin{bmatrix} 
x \cr
y \cr 
z \end{bmatrix}
$
</font>
<font color="#00FFFF" size ="5">
$\begin{bmatrix} 
s_x & 0 & 0 \cr
0 & s_y & 0 \cr 
0 & 0 & s_z \end{bmatrix}
$
</font>
<font size ="5">
$\begin{bmatrix} 
x' \cr
y' \cr 
z' \end{bmatrix}$
</font></p></p>
<p align ="right"><p align ="botton">
<font size ="5">$P'$</font>= <font color="#00FFFF" size ="5">$S$</font>$\ast$<font color="#2EFE2E" size ="5"> $P$</font>
</p></p>
<p align ="left"><font size="5">In homogeneous coordinates we get:</font></p>
<p align ="right"><p align ="botton"><font color="#2EFE2E" size ="5">
$\begin{bmatrix} 
x \cr
y \cr
z \cr 
1 \end{bmatrix}
$
</font>
<font color="#00FFFF" size ="5">
$
\begin{bmatrix} 
s_x & 0 & 0 & 0 \cr
0 & s_y & 0 & 0 \cr
0 & 0 & s_z & 0 \cr 
0 & 0 & 0 & 1 \end{bmatrix}
$
</font>
<font size ="5">
$
\begin{bmatrix} 
x' \cr
y' \cr
z' \cr 
1 \end{bmatrix}$
</font></p></p>
<p align ="right"><p align ="botton">
<font size ="5">$P'$</font>= <font color="#00FFFF" size ="5">$S$</font>$\ast$<font color="#2EFE2E" size ="5"> $P$</font>
</p></p>



